9月30日，[[中大西洋地区|中大西洋地区]]包括[[诺福克国际机场|诺福克国际机场]]、[[巴尔的摩/华盛顿瑟古德·马歇尔国际机场|巴尔的摩－华盛顿国际机场]]和[[罗纳德·里根华盛顿国家机场|罗纳德·里根华盛顿国家机场]]在内的多个地点降雨量创下新纪录，三座机场的日降雨量分别是199毫米、153毫米和118毫米<ref name="Nasa" />。马里兰州有两辆大客车在暴风雨中相撞，26名乘客受伤<ref name="ctvnews" />。[[纽约州|纽约州]]部分地区降雨量达到历史新高，估计局部雨量达到200毫米<ref name="NY">{{cite journal | volume = 55 | number = 9 | title = Storm Data and Unusual Weather Phenomena with Late Reports and Corrections | date = 2010-09 | publisher = National Climatic Data Center | accessdate = 2016-10-12 | deadurl = yes | issn = 0039-1972 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161012144323/http://www1.ncdc.noaa.gov/pub/orders/IPS/IPS-6D6D0466-A706-4481-AA98-5016C894E966.pdf | archivedate = 2016-10-12 | editor1 = Joseph E. Kraft | editor2 = Rhonda Herndon | url = http://www1.ncdc.noaa.gov/pub/orders/IPS/IPS-0D959391-5093-4B2F-8912-68B86531DA6D.pdf | format = PDF | journal =  }}[http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/IPS/sd/sd.html 此网站] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/IPS/sd/sd.html |date=20160414065723 }}可查询美国国家海洋和大气管理局风暴数据平面出版物的内容，但查询结果链接有效时间仅有24小时，用户可选择“2010-9”获得所需要的信息。</ref>，正式纪录显示[[宾汉顿|宾汉顿]]降下108毫米雨量，超越以往任何一天的24小时降雨量纪录<ref name="wpc" />。州地各地爆发山洪，导致一人溺毙，损失数额约为一万美元<ref name="NY" />。[[佛蒙特州|佛蒙特州]]和[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]同样发生相当严重的洪灾，宾夕法尼亚州的[[莫斯科_(宾夕法尼亚州)|莫斯科]]24小时降雨量达265毫米，比其他地点都高<ref name="CSM" />。残留低气压区令[[新英格兰|新英格兰]]南部的[[气压梯度|气压梯度]]加大，由此产生的狂风致使[[利奇菲尔德县_(康涅狄格州)|利奇菲尔德县]]停电，降水还令新英格兰南部发生轻度洪灾<ref>{{cite report | title = Event Record Details: High Wind | publisher = National Climatic Data Center | year = 2010 | archivedate = 2011-09-08 | accessdate = 2011-09-08 | url = http://www4.ncdc.noaa.gov/cgi-win/wwcgi.dll?wwevent~ShowEvent~833045 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110908160356/http://www4.ncdc.noaa.gov/cgi-win/wwcgi.dll?wwevent~ShowEvent~833045 | date =  }}</ref>。[[魁北克|魁北克]]降下90毫米雨量并引发洪灾，部分地下室被淹，还有两人淹死<ref name="ctvnews" />。虽然降水引发的洪灾导致人员丧生并造成破坏，但是有利于缓解旷日持久的旱情<ref name="NOAA">{{cite report | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160310043054/http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/sotc/tropical-cyclones/201009 | date = 2010-09 | url = https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/sotc/tropical-cyclones/201009 | series = State of the Climate Reports | title = Hurricanes and Tropical Storms – September 2010 | publisher = National Climatic Data Center | accessdate = 2017-01-01 | archivedate = 2016-03-10 }}</ref>。

== 善后 ==
风暴过去后，牙买加于10月5日进入[[紧急状态|紧急状态]]。[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]][[外国灾难援助办公室|外国灾难援助办公室]]提供五万美元用于购买及运送救灾物资，并提供紧急救援车辆使用的燃料<ref>{{cite report |type=Fact sheet |number=5 |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.usaid.gov/our_work/humanitarian_assistance/disaster_assistance/countries/lac/template/fs_sr/fy2011/lac_hs_fs05_10-08-2010.pdf |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zqXIIvKB?url=http://www.usaid.gov/our_work/humanitarian_assistance/disaster_assistance/countries/lac/template/fs_sr/fy2011/lac_hs_fs05_10-08-2010.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-01 |page=1 |title=Latin America and the Caribbean – Hurricane Season and Floods |publisher=[[美国国际开发署|United States Agency for International Development]] |date=2010-10-08 |accessdate=2011-07-01 }}</ref>。牙买加农业和渔业部向温室种植者协会（{{lang|en|Greenhouse Growers Association}}）捐助400万牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的4.68万美元）用于修复温室。经[[联合国粮食及农业组织|联合国粮农组织]]协助，估计有1200万牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的14.04万美元）资金及时到位，为种植约五万株庄稼幼苗提供必要资金。兽医组织向畜牧业农户提供财政援助，还向灾区派遣携带[[预防医学|预防药品]]和维生素的动物技师，防止包括山羊和绵羊在内的小型[[反刍亚目|反刍动物]]感染[[腐蹄病|腐蹄病]]。估计这些医药制品的成本为200万牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的2.34万美元）。该国香蕉委员会动用5000万牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的58.5万美元）巨灾基金，为岛上的香蕉和[[大蕉|大蕉]]种植户提供财政和人力支援。<ref>{{cite report | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084901/http://jis.gov.jm/ministry-to-provide-financial-and-technical-support-for-farmers/ | url = http://jis.gov.jm/ministry-to-provide-financial-and-technical-support-for-farmers/ | title = Ministry to Provide Financial and Technical Support for Farmers | type = Press release | publisher = Jamaica Information Service | date = 2010-10-07 | accessdate = 2017-01-02 | archivedate = 2016-03-04 }}</ref>

[[File:Road_Damage.jpg|thumb]]

气旋过去11天后，[[红十字会与红新月会国际联合会|红十字会与红新月会国际联合会]]拨款15万零644[[瑞士法郎|瑞士法郎]]（2010年瑞士法郎，相当于同年的15万6221美元），维持牙买加红十字分会向约500户家庭（约有2500人受益）发放援助及必需生活用品维生所需<ref name="dref" />。2010年12月下旬，位于[[多伦多|多伦多]]的牙买加－加拿大人协会共为灾民筹得10153.87 [[加拿大元|加拿大元]]（2010年加拿大元，相当于同年的10221.33美元）善款<ref>{{cite news | title = Jamaica-Canada group assists TS Nicole victims | url = http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20101229/news/news4.html | newspaper = The Gleaner | date = 2010-12-29 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150925123216/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20101229/news/news4.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-09-25 | accessdate = 2017-01-02 }}</ref>。汉诺威区议会申请3000万牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的35.1万美元），用于协助[[圣詹姆斯区_(牙买加)|圣詹姆斯区]]议会及其他地区有关部门的灾后清理和美化工作<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2015-09-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150925123227/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20101216/news/news4.html | deadurl = no | url = http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20101216/news/news4.html | title = Opposition calls for audit of Equalisation Funds | last = Luton | first = Daraine | date = 2010-12-16 | accessdate = 2017-01-02 | newspaper = The Gleaner }}</ref>。为了重建威斯特摩兰区的一截主干道，政府部门共拔款2.79亿牙买加元（2010年牙买加元，相当于同年的35.1万美元）<ref>{{cite report | type = Press release | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/scotts-cove-belmont-road-westmoreland-be-rehabilitated | title = Scotts Cove to Belmont Road in Westmoreland to be rehabilitated | date = 2011-08-12 | accessdate = 2017-01-02 | first = Alecia | last = Smith | work = ReliefWeb | publisher = Jamaica Information Service | archivedate = 2016-03-04 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304103717/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/scotts-cove-belmont-road-westmoreland-be-rehabilitated | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

尽管救灾工作及时，但妮科尔的影响仍然持续数月之久。牙买加的[[国内生产总值|国内生产总值]]本已深陷[[经济增长|经济增长]]放缓的泥潭，这次大范围的风灾更是雪上加霜。<ref>{{cite news |title=High growth conditionality not possible for Ja, says IMF rep |url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/business/High-growth-conditionality-not-possible-for-Ja--says-IMF-rep_8233959 |deadurl=yes |date=2010-12-15 |last=Jackson |first=Steven |accessdate=2017-01-02 |newspaper=Jamaica Observer |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064336/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/business/High-growth-conditionality-not-possible-for-Ja--says-IMF-rep_8233959 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>牙买加的农业受创很轻，只有农场养殖的鸡因风暴影响导致产蛋减少<ref>{{cite news |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080931/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/business/Imported-eggs-needed-to-ease-shortage_8231928 |url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/business/Imported-eggs-needed-to-ease-shortage_8231928 |title=Imported eggs needed to ease shortage |newspaper=Jamaica Observer |date=2010-12-15 |last=Richardson |first=Julian |accessdate=2017-01-02 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>。岛上的修复善后耗资高昂，但因风暴影响，节日季节的消费水平依然低于正常水平<ref>{{cite news | url = http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20110109/business/business5.html | title = Slow cash transactions in high-shopping season | last = Gordon | first = Sabrina | date = 2011-01-09 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150928133520/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20110109/business/business5.html | accessdate = 2017-01-02 | newspaper = The Gleaner | archivedate = 2015-09-28 }}</ref>。

